				source_str: '✻',
				caption: '',
				content: "‘Should I have said to you’; cf. 12.27 above. Some commentators take the words as a statement, ‘I would have said to you’, which is difficult to reconcile with the verse which immediately follows; others would translate, ‘I would have told you, because’; but this is a doubtful rendering of the Greek, and seems wanting in relevance. Our Lord’s thought appears to be, ‘there are places waiting in heaven for others besides myself, as you may infer from my saying that I am going to prepare a home for you’."
			},
